      "purposeInStoryline": "In Lessons 1–2 learners derived the Product and Quotient Laws and confirmed that 2⁸ × 2⁴ = 2¹² describes the Kitale farmer's maize seeds. Lesson 3 pushes deeper: What happens when the exponent is zero or negative? Can a farmer harvest 2⁰ seeds? What does 2⁻³ even mean? By introducing E. coli bacterial doubling, learners see that the same index machinery governs both explosive growth and extremely small fractional quantities, setting up the need for logarithms in Lesson 4.",
